news.title: Mumbai: Panel revived for decision on Dharavi redevelopment
news.para: According to a GR issued by the housing department, the CoS was constituted nearly 14 years ago and with the need for a speedy implementation of the project, it is being reconstituted.

news.title: Builders request Rajasthan government to remove double taxation in real estate deals
news.para: Credai-Rajasthan president Dhirendra Madan said, “The stamp duty and registration fees are charged twice for the same land which creates unnecessary burden on the buyer and investor.”

news.title: Structural audit in Gurugram: Basements of most buildings have flaws, more tests needed
news.para: DC Nishant Yadav held a meeting with the audit agencies along with representatives of RWAs and developers and department of town and country planning (DTCP) officials on Monday to discuss the report.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh police seeks extradition of Shine City owner from Dubai
news.para: Naseem, the owner of Shine City – a real estate firm, had duped investors of an estimated over Rs 350 crore by promising them flats, plots and houses which never came into being.

news.title: UK lenders see 23% slide in mortgages for home-buyers in 2023
news.para: Trade body UK Finance forecast on Monday that gross mortgage lending for house purchase would fall to 131 billion pounds ($161 billion) in 2023 from 171 billion pounds this year and a peak of 189 billion pounds in 2021, when pandemic-related tax incentives were in force.

news.title: TVS Capital's chairman buys Bengaluru residential property for Rs 15 crore
news.para: The property located at Rest House Crescent Road is spread over 6000 sq ft with 2600 sq ft built-up area. It includes a dwelling house, ouhouses, garage and other construction.

news.title: Government focusing on rehabilitation of slum dwellers: Housing minister
news.para: The policy stipulates that the eligibility for rehabilitation should be there for all 'jhuggi-jhopri' and 'bastis' which came up before January 1, 2006 and those which came up before January 1, 2015 shall not be demolished before providing compensation and no new ones are allowed to come up.

news.title: Bhopal: 430 families on the streets as houses to be demolished in Arif Nagar
news.para: District administration is scheduled to take action in Annu Nagar and new Arif Nagar. The action comes into effect without a clear and current rehabilitation plan for the displaced.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat to acquire cement assets of Jaiprakash Associates for Rs 5,666 crore
news.para: The plants have a total cement capacity of 9.4 million tonnes (MnT) along with clinker capacity of 6.7 MnT and Thermal Power plants of 280 megawatt (MW). The said plants are situated at Madhya Pradesh, Uttar Pradesh, and Chhattisgarh.

news.title: Macrotech Developers raises about Rs 3,547 crore through QIP
news.para: The promoters of Macrotech Developers have informed that following this fund raise, their shareholding in the company will be made free of all encumbrances.

news.title: Aqua Line's Greater Noida Extension gets public investment board nod
news.para: This is the first of the two proposed extensions of the Aqua Line, the other being the expressway arm from Sector 142 to Botanical Garden, whose alignment and other aspects are yet to be finalised.

news.title: Chandigarh: To raise IT Park housing project, CHB to go to centre again
news.para: “All the projects are approved in the Chandigarh Master Plan-2031. They follow the notification of the ESZ and other wildlife norms. The site is located 1.25 km away from the ESZ. In fact, it is around 1.56 km away,” an official claimed.

news.title: Colonies in Hubballi crippled, lack basic facilities
news.para: The areas are on Kusugal Road, about 5 km from the city centre, and were planned out about 20 years ago. Nearly 4,000 families live in this area and are deprived of basic facilities.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body slashes plot prices to woo public
news.para: A state-level committee fixed ₹18,000 per square yard price for the sale of 446 plots in the layout being developed by the Visakhapatnam Metropolitan Region Development Authority (VMRDA) in Palavalasa village near Anandapuram in Vizag suburbs.

news.title: Chandigarh administration's review meeting on master plan 2031 on Dec 13
news.para: Even after almost seven years of coming up with the master plan, most projects remain only on paper. Making them a reality is the challenging task for the authorities.
